<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>

<p><a href="http:www.redellipse.net/code/fortune">fortune</a> is a simple program that displays random, poignant, inspirational, silly or malicious phrases from a citation database. The fortune command line utility is part of the <a href="https://packages.gentoo.org/packages/games-misc/fortune-mod">games-misc/fortune-mod package</a>.</p>

<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>

<p>Fortune is available from the repository of all <strong>Linux</strong>  distributions and all <strong>BSD</strong>. So to install use the same:</p>

<!-- QUADRADO -->
<script async="" src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>

<p><ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:inline-block;width:336px;height:280px" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2838251107855362" data-ad-slot="5351066970"></ins>
